<TITLE> Low in Bay, seaports hoist signal 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com)A low forming in the Bay of Bengal Sunday gave rise to the possibility of squally winds to blow over the sea ports in the south, met office said. Chittagong, Cox's Bazaar and Mongla maritime ports have been asked to hoist local cautionary signal three and the fishing boats and trawlers have been advised to stay safely anchored till further notice. The weathermen said some places in the country may have temporary gusty to squally winds accompanied by moderate rainfall to thundershowers. The day temperature will remain more or less unchanged. The highest temperature Saturday was recorded at Chuadanga (35.7 degree C) and the lowest in Rangpur (24.8 degree C). The sun sets Sunday at 6"49 pm and rises at 5:20 am monday. 
